<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>{{title}}</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body {
            background-image: url('https://pixy.org/src2/595/5953111.jpg');
            background-size: cover;
            background-position: center;
            background-attachment: fixed;
            background-repeat: no-repeat;
            color: white;
            position: relative;
        }

        body::before {
            content: "";
            position: absolute;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            right: 0;
            bottom: 0;
            background-image: inherit;
            background-size: inherit;
            background-position: inherit;
            background-attachment: inherit;
            background-repeat: inherit;
            filter: blur(8px); 
            z-index: -1;
        }

        .text-box {
            background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            color: white;
            margin-bottom: 20px; 
        }

        .carousel-item img {
            object-fit: cover;
            height: 400px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container mt-4">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div class="text-box">
                    <h1 class="text-left">{{title}}</h1>
                    <h2>Summary of the work</h2>
                    <p>This project is part of the programming course: Introduction to Web Programming of the Lisbon Institute of Engineering (ISEL).</p>
                    <p>This is the second of three development cycles of the FOCCACIA application.</p>
                    <p>The main objectives of this phase include:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Add a web interface to FOCCACIA, which was initially developed only as an API in the first part.</li>
                        <li>Store data in a database, replacing storage in previously used memory.</li>
                        <li>Incorporate new technologies and techniques approached in the classes, improving the functionality and efficiency of the application.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Functional requirements include the need to allow more than one group with the same name to be created regardless of the proprietary user.</p>
                    <p>In addition, you should create a new feature that returns specific details of a team, including name, image, stadium name and the leagues in which the team participated.</p>
                    <p>This work aims to deepen students' knowledge in web development, integrating user interfaces, data persistence and modern programming practices.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="text-box text-center d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center">
                    <div class="me-4">
                        <p>Work done by Henrique Seara and Lourenço Teles.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="me-4">
                        <a href="https://github.com/kikobangarang" target="_blank">
                            <img src="https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIP.uwTXeoRua-yoEcS-HY40QgHaHa?rs=1&pid=ImgDetMain" 
                                 alt="Descrição da imagem" class="img-fluid rounded img-small">
                        </a>
                        <p class="mt-2">Henrique Seara.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="ms-4">
                        <a href="https://github.com/LourencoTeles8" target="_blank">
                            <img src="https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIP.uwTXeoRua-yoEcS-HY40QgHaHa?rs=1&pid=ImgDetMain" 
                                 alt="Descrição da imagem" class="img-fluid rounded img-small">
                        </a>
                        <p class="mt-2">Lourenço Teles.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <style>
                    .img-small {
                        max-width: 150px; 
                        max-height: 150px; 
                    }
                </style>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div id="imageCarousel" class="carousel slide carousel-fade" data-bs-ride="carousel" data-bs-interval="3000">
                    <div class="carousel-inner">
                        <div class="carousel-item active">
                            <img src="https://escolaeducacao.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/futebol-brasil.jpg" class="d-block w-100 rounded" alt="Futebol Brasil">
                        </div>
                        <div class="carousel-item">
